ocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529467\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104laf1665702704418.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/laf1665702704418.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/laf1665702704418.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"laf1665702704418\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n       Locking Support on Informix\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To use locking, ensure that your database enables transaction logging. If not, use\n      U_VERSION. All locking types (optimistic, cautious, and paranoid) are supported. The default\n      locking type is cautious; the locking granularity is set to row locking.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"laf1665702704418__section_ncx_1t2_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d604315e51\">Special considerations</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"laf1665702704418__p_d50840e1_d50841e1_d50842e1\">Informix cannot lock records in the way that Uniface\n            requires, unless transaction logging is enabled. When transaction logging is enabled,\n            the connector makes sure that you are always in a transaction.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"laf1665702704418__p_d50843e1_d50844e1_d50845e1\">You should also be aware that Informix has a maximum\n            number of locks which can be simultaneously held. The maximum depends on the operating\n            system in use and the way in which you have configured Informix. For more information,\n            see your Informix documentation.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"laf1665702704418__section_d4l_ct2_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d604315e63\">U_VERSION</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"laf1665702704418__p_d50849e1_d50850e1_d50851e1\">It is recommended that you use U_VERSION as this\n            significantly reduces the chance of locking conflicts.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cwe1665702704830.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>U_VERSION for Improving Locking Performance</a><p>Uniface supports a version mechanism which can improve performance by using a field called U_VERSION. U_VERSION is a one-byte field which you must assign to an entity for it to work. In other words, it is not automatically available.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529467\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529467\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Locking Support on Informix Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Locking Support on Informix To use locking, ensure that your database enables transaction logging. If not, use U_VERSION. All locking types (optimistic, cautious, and paranoid) are supported. The default locking type is cautious; the locking granularity is set to row locking. Special considerations Informix cannot lock records in the way that Uniface requires, unless transaction logging is enabled. When transaction logging is enabled, the connector makes sure that you are always in a transaction. You should also be aware that Informix has a maximum number of locks which can be simultaneously held. The maximum depends on the operating system in use and the way in which you have configured Informix. For more information, see your Informix documentation. U_VERSION It is recommended that you use U_VERSION as this significantly reduces the chance of locking conflicts. Related Links U_VERSION for Improving Locking Performance Uniface supports a version mechanism which can improve performance by using a field called U_VERSION. U_VERSION is a one-byte field which you must assign to an entity for it to work. In other words, it is not automatically available. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}